`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.blockquote,{children:[`
`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:'The return type of an async function is a unique anonymous type generated by the compiler, similar to the type of a closure. You can think of this type as being like an enum, with one variant for every "yield point" of the function - the beginning of it, the await expressions, and every return. Each variant stores the state that is needed to be stored to resume control from that yield point.'}),`
