`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:"Creating/Composing a future object (for example, by calling an async function which calls another async function) does not involve any progress. Only when you pass it to something that actively polls it, the future object starts its work and makes progress (poll by poll). At that point, we refer to the whole future thingy as a task. A suspension point simply makes a call to the future's poll method return immediately with a Poll::Pending value if the value is not ready yet."}),`
`]}),`
